check.action:
Output an agent-orchestration block that includes two participants per repo (pm + architect) and one additional ux-designer for each frontend repo. Replace the example repo names below with the actual repo names.

```agent-orchestration
{
      "mode": "orchestration",
  "round_state": "dispatching",
  "parallel": true,
  "participants": [
    {
      "agent": "pm",
      "provider": "current",
      "reason": "analyze repo-a from the product angle",
      "focus": "repo-a only. Identify users, capabilities, workflows, business value, maturity clues, and product-facing gaps grounded in repo-a files. Name all users, personas, features, and capabilities in {{document_language}}. Write findings to `.agent-work/pm_analysis__repo-a.md` using your native Write tool."
    },
    {
      "agent": "architect",
      "provider": "current",
      "reason": "analyze repo-a from the architecture angle",
      "focus": "repo-a only. Produce a thorough technical slice covering: (1) Stack — runtime, language, framework versions, build toolchain, test framework; (2) Entry points — main processes, bootstrap files, config files; (3) Module map — top-level directories with one-line role per module; (4) API surface — list every exposed endpoint or event contract (REST routes with method+path+purpose, GraphQL types, event names+payload shape, MCP tools if any); (5) Data stores — DBs, schemas, ORM models, migration strategy; (6) Key conventions — naming, layering, error handling, auth patterns grounded in actual code; (7) Hotspots and risks — large/complex/coupled files; (8) Repo boundaries — what this repo owns vs delegates. All labels and names in {{document_language}}. Write findings to `.agent-work/architect_analysis__repo-a.md` using your native Write tool."
    },
    {
      "agent": "pm",
      "provider": "current",
      "reason": "analyze repo-b from the product angle",
      "focus": "repo-b only. Identify users, capabilities, workflows, business value, maturity clues, and product-facing gaps grounded in repo-b files. Name all users, personas, features, and capabilities in {{document_language}}. Write findings to `.agent-work/pm_analysis__repo-b.md` using your native Write tool."
    },
    {
      "agent": "architect",
      "provider": "current",
      "reason": "analyze repo-b from the architecture angle",
      "focus": "repo-b only. Produce a thorough technical slice covering: (1) Stack — runtime, language, framework versions, build toolchain, test framework; (2) Entry points — main processes, bootstrap files, config files; (3) Module map — top-level directories with one-line role per module; (4) API surface — list every exposed endpoint or event contract (REST routes with method+path+purpose, GraphQL types, event names+payload shape, MCP tools if any); (5) Data stores — DBs, schemas, ORM models, migration strategy; (6) Key conventions — naming, layering, error handling, auth patterns grounded in actual code; (7) Hotspots and risks — large/complex/coupled files; (8) Repo boundaries — what this repo owns vs delegates. All labels and names in {{document_language}}. Write findings to `.agent-work/architect_analysis__repo-b.md` using your native Write tool."
    },
    {
      "agent": "ux-designer",
      "provider": "current",
      "reason": "analyze the frontend repo(s) for design system and UX patterns",
      "focus": "frontend repos only (those containing HTML, CSS/SCSS, or a component library). Produce a UX and design system analysis covering: (1) Component library used and version; (2) Color palette — extract all color tokens, CSS variables, or Tailwind config values (primary, secondary, neutral, semantic colors); (3) Typography — font families, size scale, weight conventions; (4) Spacing and layout system — grid, breakpoints, spacing scale; (5) Component inventory — list recurring UI components (buttons, forms, tables, modals, nav…) with their location and observed states/variants; (6) Icon set used; (7) UI patterns per feature area — which views exist, what layout they use, what interactions are present (grounded in actual HTML/template files); (8) Design inconsistencies or gaps observed. All labels and names in {{document_language}}. Write findings to `.agent-work/ux_analysis__{repo_name}.md` using your native Write tool."
    }
  ],
  "shared_context": {
    "scope": "repo-scoped full workspace analysis",
    "repos": ["repo-a", "repo-b"],
    "document_language": "{{document_language}}",
    "user_goal": "Understand what this product does today — product and technical perspective. All named artifacts (personas, features, capabilities) must be in {{document_language}}."
  },
  "synthesis_goal": "Each scoped runner writes repo-specific findings to `.agent-work/{agent}__{repo}.md` files. Once all repo-scoped PM and Architect runners complete, the coordinator reads those files and performs the final workspace-level synthesis with Analyst discipline."
}
```

step.action:
Build {{product_md}} content in {{document_language}}:

      "# Product — {{workspace_name}}
      > Generated by Nakiros on {date}. Refresh with /nak-workflow-generate-context.

      ## Vision
      {What the product does and the problem it solves — 2-4 sentences grounded in code evidence.}

      ## Users
      See personas.md

      ## Core Principles
      {3-5 guiding principles inferred from the codebase: architecture choices, UX patterns, domain model.}

      ## Repo Responsibilities
      {How each repo contributes to the product — one line per repo.}

      ## Current Maturity
      {early prototype / MVP / production-ready / scaling — with evidence}

      ## Gaps and Unknowns
      {What is missing, unclear, or needs validation — product and technical perspectives.}"

Build {{personas_md}} content in {{document_language}} by deduplicating actors found across all repos:
      ALL persona names and field labels MUST be written in {{document_language}}.

      "# Personas — {{workspace_name}}
      > Generated by Nakiros on {date}. Refresh with /nak-workflow-generate-context.

      ## {Persona Name in {{document_language}}}
      {Who they are in one sentence — in {{document_language}}.}
      Needs: {what they need from the product — in {{document_language}}}
      Frustrations: {current pain or friction points — in {{document_language}}}
      Context: {when and how they interact — in {{document_language}}}

      [repeat for each distinct persona]"

Build {{features_list}} — one entry per main capability identified across the workspace.
    For each feature, prepare:
      - name: feature name in {{document_language}}
      - slug: lowercase-hyphenated folder name derived from the {{document_language}} name (transliterate accents, e.g. "Gestion des équipes" → "gestion-des-equipes")
      - existing: true if folder already exists in {{existing_features}}, false otherwise
      - content in {{document_language}} — ALL section headers, labels, and text MUST be in {{document_language}}:

      "# Feature: {Feature Name in {{document_language}}}
      {What this feature does and the value it brings to users — in {{document_language}} — 1-3 sentences grounded in evidence.}

      ## Capacités actuelles
      - {capability 1 — file path evidence}
      - {capability 2}
      ...

      ## Repos impliqués
      {which repos contribute to this feature}

      ## Dépendances
      {features this depends on, or 'Aucune'}

      ## Stories
      | ID | Titre | Statut |
      |----|-------|--------|
      | — | À définir | 📋 À planifier |

      ---
      Generated by Nakiros product-discovery on {date}. Update with /nak-workflow-pm-feature."

    For each feature that has frontend code evidence in the UX analysis, also prepare a {{feature.ux_content}} in {{document_language}}:

      "# UX — {Feature Name in {{document_language}}}
      > Discovered by Nakiros product-discovery on {date}. Refine with /nak-workflow-create-ux-design.

      ## Existing Screens
      {List of view/page files that implement this feature, with path — grounded in actual files found}

      ## Components Used
      {UI components observed in those views}

      ## Key Interactions
      {Forms, tables, modals, navigation patterns observed in the code}

      ## Layout
      {Layout approach — full-page, sidebar, modal, drawer…}

      ## Empty & Error States
      {How empty states or errors are handled, if found — or 'Not observed'}

      ## UX Gaps
      {Interactions or states missing or inconsistent compared to the declared capabilities}

      ---
      This file was bootstrapped from existing code. Run /nak-workflow-create-ux-design to produce a full UX specification."

    If no frontend code is found for a feature, set {{feature.ux_content}} to null — do not create the file.

If at least one {{ux_analysis__*}} key was found, build {{design_system_md}} content in {{document_language}} by merging all UX Designer findings across frontend repos.
    If {{existing_design_system}} was loaded in step 1, enrich it rather than replacing it.
    Content template:

      "# Design System — {{workspace_name}}
      > Generated by Nakiros on {date}. Refresh with /nak-workflow-generate-context.

      ## Component Library
      {Name, version, installation method — grounded in package.json or equivalent}

      ## Color Palette
      | Token / Variable | Value | Usage |
      |-----------------|-------|-------|
      {rows extracted from CSS variables, Tailwind config, or design token files — primary, secondary, neutral, semantic (success, warning, error, info)}

      ## Typography
      | Role | Font Family | Size | Weight |
      |------|------------|------|--------|
      {rows: heading-1 through body-sm, monospace if any}

      ## Spacing & Layout
      - **Grid system** : {columns, gutter, container max-width}
      - **Breakpoints** : {xs/sm/md/lg/xl values}
      - **Spacing scale** : {base unit and scale, e.g. 4px base, Tailwind scale}

      ## Icon Set
      {Library name and version, or 'No icon library detected'}

      ## Component Inventory
      | Component | Location | Variants observed |
      |-----------|----------|-------------------|
      {rows: one per recurring UI component — button, input, table, modal, badge, toast, nav…}

      ## UI Patterns
      {Recurring layout or interaction patterns found across feature areas — e.g. master-detail, wizard, inline edit, confirm modal}

      ## Design Inconsistencies & Gaps
      {Observed inconsistencies — mixed styling approaches, untokenized hardcoded colors, components with diverging behavior across feature areas}

      ---
      Generated by Nakiros product-discovery on {date}. Update with /nak-workflow-create-ux-design."
    If no UX analysis was found (no frontend repos), set {{design_system_md}} to null — do not write the file.

For EACH repo analyzed in step 2, build a per-repo architecture slice {{architecture_slice__{repo_slug}}} in {{document_language}}.
    Use the slug: lowercase-hyphenated repo name (e.g. "kpe-back" → "kpe-back").
    Content template:

      "# Architecture — {repo_name}
      > Generated by Nakiros on {date}. Refresh with /nak-workflow-generate-context.

      ## Stack
      | Layer | Technology | Version |
      |-------|-----------|---------|
      {rows from architect analysis: runtime, language, framework, build tool, test framework}

      ## Entry Points
      {bootstrap file(s), main process, config files — with path}

      ## Module Map
      | Module / Directory | Role |
      |--------------------|------|
      {one row per top-level directory or significant module}

      ## API Surface
      {If REST: table with Method | Route | Purpose}
      {If events: table with Event | Direction | Payload shape}
      {If MCP tools: table with Tool name | Input | Output}
      {If GraphQL: list types and resolvers}
      Note: only what is actually found in code — no speculation.

      ## Data Stores
      {DB type, ORM, schema location, migration approach}

      ## Conventions
      {Naming conventions, layering rules, auth pattern, error handling — grounded in file evidence}

      ## Hotspots & Risks
      {Files or modules that are large, complex, or tightly coupled — with brief reason}

      ## Boundaries
      {What this repo owns vs what it delegates to other repos or services}

      ---
      Generated by Nakiros product-discovery on {date}."

Write the following files using your native Write tool (create parent directories as needed):
      - `{{preview_root}}/product.md` ← {{product_md}}
      - `{{preview_root}}/personas.md` ← {{personas_md}}
      - For each feature in {{features_list}}: `{{preview_root}}/features/{slug}/feature.md` ← feature content
      - For each feature with non-null ux_content: `{{preview_root}}/features/{slug}/ux.md` ← ux content
      - `{{preview_root}}/architecture/index.md` ← {{architecture_index}}
      - For each repo analyzed: `{{preview_root}}/architecture/{repo_slug}/index.md` ← architecture slice
      - `{{preview_root}}/design-system.md` ← {{design_system_md}} (only if not null)

